The paper deals with the consensus problem for multiple robotic systems, which is a core topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also addresses the issues of uncertain kinematics and dynamics, which are related to control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.MA). The proposed observer-based adaptive controller involves the use of distributed adaptive kinematic regressor matrix, which is a machine learning technique (cs.MA). The paper also formalizes the concept of manipulability, which is related to optimization and machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
